"{\"uid\": \"forbes.com-sites-katewieczorek-2024-07-31-unlike-the-2024-olympics-female-dominated-industries-undervalue-women\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"ByKate Wieczorek,  Contributor.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 31, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Forthe first time in Olympic history, the 2024 Paris Olympics showcase an equal split of male and female global athletes.\", \"from\": 33, \"to\": 154, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team USA has sent 314 women and 278 men, a 53/47 percent split.\", \"from\": 155, \"to\": 218, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 155, \"end\": 163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999901591996, \"rank\": 9.28751334466637e-08, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With the passing ofEqual Pay for Team USA Act in 2022, gender equality is at the forefront of the American Olympic team.\", \"from\": 219, \"to\": 339, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 317, \"end\": 338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_at_the_2022_Winter_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.6805559871140412, \"rank\": 0.3903307518945794, \"text\": \"American Olympic team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_at_the_2022_Winter_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_at_the_2022_Winter_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, this has not translated to U.S. jobs, even in predominately female industries.\", \"from\": 340, \"to\": 427, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Healthcare workers and related technical occupations possess the altruistic and difficult mission of keeping us healthy and well.\", \"from\": 429, \"to\": 558, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even though women represent almost 50 percentage points more in the industry, men make nearly double the average salary of women in this field.\", \"from\": 559, \"to\": 702, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Source:Data USA  Additional education could necessitate a higher salary, however, this is not the case.\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 811, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 715, \"end\": 723, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Data_USA\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Data USA\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Data_USA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Data_USA\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The number of women achieving educational degrees in healthcare greatly outnumber the number of men, regardless of the type of degree awarded (Figure 1).\", \"from\": 812, \"to\": 965, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to theAmerican Association of University Women, at the current rate of progress it will take until 2088 to close the gender pay gap.\", \"from\": 969, \"to\": 1111, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The marketing industry is also contributing to unequal pay.Despite women occupying 61% of the industry, men collect nearly an extra $32,000 when comparing average salaries.\", \"from\": 1112, \"to\": 1284, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Source:Data USA  Marketing analysts have been primarily female for over 10 years.\", \"from\": 1290, \"to\": 1371, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1297, \"end\": 1305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Data_USA\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Data USA\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Data_USA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Data_USA\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since 2014, women have held at least a 14 percentage point lead above men (Figure 2) yet continue to be underpaid.\", \"from\": 1372, \"to\": 1486, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite women holding nearly 80% of these jobs, elementary and middle school male teachers make nearly 13% more than their female cohorts.\", \"from\": 1490, \"to\": 1628, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Furthermore, early education female teachers work on average 1.5 hours more per week, according toresearch published in Frontiers in Psychology.\", \"from\": 1629, \"to\": 1773, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Source:Data USA  Female elementary and middle school teachers not only paid less than their male counterparts, but also fall $7,350 short ofthe average salary the U.S. workers.\", \"from\": 1779, \"to\": 1955, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1786, \"end\": 1794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Data_USA\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Data USA\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Data_USA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Data_USA\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is particularly debilitating considering that teachers work more hours per week than other working adults, according toa 2023 American Teacher Survey  Every business needs Human Resource (HR) Managers.\", \"from\": 1956, \"to\": 2162, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2087, \"end\": 2103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Teacher\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"American Teacher\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Teacher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Teacher\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. Bureau of Labor anticipate a 5% job growth for HR Managers between 2022 - 2032, higher than the projected rate for all occupations.\", \"from\": 2163, \"to\": 2303, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While women account for 70% of Human Resource Managers, they earn nearly 15% less than their male coworkers.\", \"from\": 2304, \"to\": 2412, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Source:Data USA  As organizations continue to focus on attracting and retaining top talent, effective Human Resource management isessential to a company's success.\", \"from\": 2418, \"to\": 2581, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2425, \"end\": 2433, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Data_USA\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Data USA\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Data_USA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Data_USA\"}, {\"begin\": 2526, \"end\": 2545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Resource_management\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Resource management\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Resource_management\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Resource_management\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Businesses need to reassess how they are compensating female leaders in HR.\", \"from\": 2582, \"to\": 2657, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is not an exhaustive list of every female-dominated industry that is slacking in paying women.\", \"from\": 2659, \"to\": 2758, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Overall, the U.S. gender pay gap is stifling and stagnant - with women earning around80 cents for every dollar men earnedfor the past two decades.\", \"from\": 2759, \"to\": 2905, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2024 Olympics gives us hope that with systemic changes and continued advocacy, we can move the needle forward toward closing the gender pay gap.\", \"from\": 2906, \"to\": 3054, \"entities\": []}]}"